Defendant Obed L Garcia Rivera in court with attorney Michael Reyes.  John Woodson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Patrick Ryan appeared as interpreter.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty. Attorney Reyes requests expungement of the cases.  The State takes no position.   The Court denies the request for expungement. 
  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS JAIL;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling; 
*No violent contact with: C.S.;  
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Defendant not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed;
*Domestic Violence Counseling;

COURT COSTS:  $343.00 (includes domestic abuse surcharge-to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 2 DAYS (apply 2 days credit) TIME SERVED.
